description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team members are adaptable, friendly, polite and caring. They enjoy working as a team with people from different cultures and backgrounds. Do you share these values? Then we could have just the role for you. We are looking for a Health Care Assistant to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Practice Plus Hospital, Shepton Mallet we create an exceptional experience for all patients and are dedicated to delivering the highest standards of quality and safety. We have been rated Outstanding by the CQC, putting it at the very top of the regulator’s quality ratings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supported by our Patient Admissions Team and Clinical Triage Lead, Eleanor, you will assist with the pre-operative case management. This will include using your clinical skills to ensure that patients are fit for their procedures, maintaining accurate patient records, making pre-operative phone calls to patients and offering administrative support to the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have completed your NVQ Level 3 in Health and Social Care or be willing to work towards it and hold your BLS certificate. Recent experience working as a Health Care Assistant in an acute setting is essential in this role. Above all, you have a natural ability to help make the lives of others more fulfilling, the ability to work as part of a multidisciplinary team, excellent communication skills and the desire to work in an environment where the work can be hard, but also fun and rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Practice Plus Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everything we do is focused on providing a high standard of safe and effective patient care. Our facilities are modern, employing the latest technology with friendly and professional staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want our team members to feel motivated and rewarded. So we offer a competitive package of pay and benefits. We also recognise the value of a healthy work-life balance – so we always try to be flexible, helping you fit your working life around your home life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for the role click on the link below. If you have any questions contact Sonia Sanghvi in our friendly resourcing team.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will contact all shortlisted candidate but please note Practice Plus Group retain the right to remove the advert prior to the closing date if a suitable candidate is appointed. Our employment offers are subject to receipt of satisfactory pre-employment checks. At Practice Plus Group, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities. Applicants must have the right to work in the EU.&lt;/p&gt;
